RONALD CLARK WAS A BLACK CHILD IN THE 1940'S.
HIS FATHER WAS THE CUSTODIAN FOR A LIBRARY IN WASHINGTON HEIGHTS.
HIS FATHER TOOK GREAT CARE OF THE LIBRARY, KEEPING IT SPOTLESS AND EVEN WAXING THE TOPS OF THE BOOKSHELVES.
RONALD THOUGHT HIS FAMILY WAS RICH GROWING UP BUT THEY WERE POOR.
RONALD DIDN'T INVITE KIDS TO COME OVER AND THEY THOUGHT HE LIVED IN THE LIBRARY.
RONALD LOVED BOOKS AND THEY MADE HIM WANT TO LEARN.
RONALD WAS THE FIRST OF HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL AND THE FIRST TO GO TO COLLEGE.
